## Prerequisites

- Go 1.21+
- Docker & Docker Compose

## Getting Started

```bash
# Quick setup (starts DB, installs deps, runs migrations)
make setup

# Or manually:
make docker-up
make migrate
make run
```

The server starts at http://localhost:8080.

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path             | Description        |
|--------|------------------|--------------------|
| GET    | /health          | Health check       |
| GET    | /api/v1/users    | List all users     |
| GET    | /api/v1/posts    | List all posts     |

## Project Structure

```
cmd/server/           - HTTP server entrypoint
cmd/migrate/          - Database migration tool
internal/config/      - Configuration loading
internal/database/    - Database connection and pooling
internal/models/      - GORM models (User, Post)
internal/repository/  - Repository pattern for data access
migrations/           - SQL migration reference files
scripts/              - Setup and utility scripts
pkg/                  - Public library code
docs/supporting/      - Project documentation
```

## Database

This project uses GORM with PostgreSQL. Models use UUID primary keys and soft deletes.

### Models
- **User**: email, name, has many posts
- **Post**: title, body, published flag, belongs to user

### Migrations
GORM AutoMigrate handles schema changes. SQL files in `migrations/` serve as documentation of the intended schema.

## Make Commands

```bash
make run          # Run the application
make build        # Build binary
make migrate      # Run database migrations
make setup        # Full setup (DB + deps + migrations)
make test         # Run tests
make coverage     # Run tests with coverage
make fmt          # Format code
make vet          # Vet code
make docker-up    # Start PostgreSQL
make docker-down  # Stop PostgreSQL
make tidy         # Tidy Go modules
make clean        # Clean build artifacts
```
